parameters:
Zena: Luuna, at this rate, you're at a disadvantage. You're battered
and outnumbered.

Zena: So, here's the game. If you can beat one of us three, I'll let
you escape.
Zena: If you can win, that is.
Zena: So, who will you choose?

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] (Of course, among them, Zena has the lowest magical power, but
I have no information on Zena... However, with my current strength, I
absolutely can't win against Lucia and Sylvia.)

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] (If it's true that Regnus Grahardt was defeated by Zena, I want
to know why. It's okay if I don't win. I just need to grasp Zena's
secret and then retreat.)

Zena: If you can kill me, we from Valentia will withdraw from
Jupiterino.

Zena: I promise to honor it. After all, I am the prince of the great
magical nation of Valentia. But only if you can kill me.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] That's more than I could wish for.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] (The rumor that Regnus Grahardt was defeated by Zena...)
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] (If it's true, this magic should reveal it...!)
Zena: That was an incredible attack... I'm surprised.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] It didn't seem to... affect you much...

Zena: You see, I was born with a unique constitution that makes me
tough. It was an incredible attack, but I managed to withstand it.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] That can't be... (It's not about being tough... Why...)
Zena: Luuna, my technique may be plain compared to yours.

Zena: "Threads of Death." With these threads, I'll tear you apart.
Luuna, you've lost.

Zena: If you move, your body will be torn apart. The threads are
sharper than any blade.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] It seems this match will end in a draw.

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Prince Zena, if the plague-bringer like you dies, Jupiterino
and Valentina will return to their peaceful ways as before.
Zena: It's not a draw. Try pulling on the threads.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Zena! Die by your own technique!
